The Cosafa Castle Cup organising committee have announced that tickets for the remaining first round matches at the 2017 tournament in South Africa s North West province will be FREE to the public. This includes all matches from Tuesday, June 27 through to the end of the pool phase on Friday, June 30.Fans wishing to attend the games must still obtain a ticket from Computicket at Shoprite/ Checkers stores nationwide, or at www.computicket.co.za.Tickets provide entry to the stadium on match day and can be used to watch both games in the case of a double-header. Sport24.